Actually, we still want to know how everyone feels about these pun-based names.

80
00:03:03,810 --> 00:03:04,735
How well are they accepted?

81
00:03:04,735 --> 00:03:05,260
For example,

82
00:03:05,660 --> 00:03:06,810
if it's a four-character name,

83
00:03:06,810 --> 00:03:07,960
or some really long names,

84
00:03:07,960 --> 00:03:09,010
people might not remember them.

85
00:03:09,360 --> 00:03:11,285
So, you just mentioned acceptance.

86
00:03:11,285 --> 00:03:14,210
How do the guests react to their own names?

87
00:03:14,460 --> 00:03:14,785
Hmm.

88
00:03:14,785 --> 00:03:15,960
When they look at the card,

89
00:03:15,960 --> 00:03:19,085
since the first thing on the card is the name,

90
00:03:19,085 --> 00:03:20,785
they find the name really funny.

91
00:03:20,785 --> 00:03:22,360
Then they start laughing.

92
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:23,850
When you see them laugh,

93
00:03:23,850 --> 00:03:24,475
you feel really happy.

94
00:03:24,475 --> 00:03:25,025
You just feel like

95
00:03:25,025 --> 00:03:26,525
the name you came up with is pretty good.

96
00:03:26,525 --> 00:03:28,150
Because they also think it's interesting.

97
00:03:28,950 --> 00:03:29,350
Yeah.

98
00:03:29,600 --> 00:03:31,350
So after episode 8 aired,

99
00:03:31,350 --> 00:03:33,450
everyone thought the relationship lines were really complicated.

100
00:03:33,800 --> 00:03:37,025
People said that the PDs must have gone crazy from work.

101
00:03:37,025 --> 00:03:40,675
To come up with such chaotic and dramatic relationship lines.

102
00:03:40,675 --> 00:03:42,350
So I wanted to ask,

103
00:03:42,840 --> 00:03:44,465
was it like coming up with names back then?

104
00:03:44,465 --> 00:03:47,690
Did we plan out a lot of different relationships in advance?

105
00:03:48,190 --> 00:03:48,490
Yeah.

106
00:03:48,490 --> 00:03:49,515
Just like this question,

107
00:03:49,515 --> 00:03:52,165
how did you come up with such intertwined relationship lines at the time?

108
00:03:52,165 --> 00:03:53,340
Were the PDs crazy?

109
00:03:53,490 --> 00:03:54,440
Our answer is,

110
00:03:54,590 --> 00:03:55,390
Yes, we were.

111
00:03:55,390 --> 00:03:55,865
Crazy.

112
00:03:55,865 --> 00:03:56,590
Totally crazy.

113
00:03:57,090 --> 00:03:59,590
The more we created, the crazier we got.

114
00:04:00,140 --> 00:04:01,090
The more we created, the more excited we became.

115
00:04:02,960 --> 00:04:04,660
Yesterday, I even saw a comment online

116
00:04:04,760 --> 00:04:08,660
saying that Bai Ge never called Ke Yu "dad."

117
00:04:08,660 --> 00:04:10,510
Like, did he accept this or not?

118
00:04:10,560 --> 00:04:11,535
The whole "acknowledging a father" thing.

119
00:04:11,535 --> 00:04:13,885
Is it because he got the script for episode 7 later on

120
00:04:13,885 --> 00:04:14,935
and found out he wasn't actually the son?

121
00:04:14,935 --> 00:04:16,185
So that's why he didn't acknowledge it?

122
00:04:16,185 --> 00:04:17,410
No, he was just being stubborn.

123
00:04:17,810 --> 00:04:19,760
It's really just his last bit of stubbornness.

124
00:04:19,920 --> 00:04:20,270
Stubborn.

125
00:04:20,270 --> 00:04:20,870
Stubborn.

126
00:04:21,420 --> 00:04:23,020
So when everyone sees these kinds of relationships,

127
00:04:23,020 --> 00:04:24,620
are they okay with it?

128
00:04:24,620 --> 00:04:26,945
Or do they sometimes complain about it afterwards?

129
00:04:26,945 --> 00:04:28,320
Or are they actually happy about it?

130
00:04:28,920 --> 00:04:30,870
They think it's really fun.

131
00:04:31,420 --> 00:04:33,370
They find it interesting too.

132
00:04:33,420 --> 00:04:33,820
Yeah.

133
00:04:34,070 --> 00:04:35,820
They probably just think we're crazy.

134
00:04:37,270 --> 00:04:40,320
Actually, everyone's relationships have gotten better this season.

135
00:04:40,540 --> 00:04:43,740
And everyone is getting more and more invested in the filming.

136
00:04:43,740 --> 00:04:45,665
So we have to mention

137
00:04:45,665 --> 00:04:47,690
our teacher Bai Yu.

138
00:04:47,890 --> 00:04:50,890
We'd also like to invite you to share with us

139
00:04:51,140 --> 00:04:55,365
some stories about Bai Ge during the whole filming process.

140
00:04:55,365 --> 00:04:59,040
First, let's start with a question from a fan.

141
00:04:59,040 --> 00:04:59,540
So,

142
00:05:00,100 --> 00:05:01,150
after three seasons,

143
00:05:01,200 --> 00:05:04,850
do you think Bai Yu has become more mature or more childish?

144
00:05:05,200 --> 00:05:08,950
I can't directly say he's become more childish or more mature.

145
00:05:09,550 --> 00:05:13,250
Because I don't think it's a simple feeling.

146
00:05:13,400 --> 00:05:14,950
Because in every season,

147
00:05:14,950 --> 00:05:17,500
there are both mature and childish sides.

148
00:05:17,750 --> 00:05:19,875
It's because we've reached the third season now.

149
00:05:19,875 --> 00:05:20,600
And everyone

150
00:05:21,080 --> 00:05:21,330
um,

151
00:05:21,930 --> 00:05:23,430
has become more and more familiar with each other.

152
00:05:23,430 --> 00:05:25,130
And we've also grown closer.

153
00:05:25,180 --> 00:05:28,480
So I think it's because of this environment and atmosphere

154
00:05:28,480 --> 00:05:31,230
that he feels more secure.

155
00:05:31,230 --> 00:05:32,530
And more at ease.

156
00:05:32,530 --> 00:05:32,905
So,

157
00:05:32,905 --> 00:05:37,505
he's more willing to show his childlike side,

158
00:05:37,505 --> 00:05:40,330
and his more childish side to everyone.

159
00:05:40,740 --> 00:05:41,090
And

160
00:05:41,290 --> 00:05:45,340
maybe that's why people feel that Bai Ge seems more childish in the third season.

161
00:05:45,340 --> 00:05:45,840
But

162
00:05:45,840 --> 00:05:49,340
actually, even though he sometimes looks very steady,

163
00:05:49,340 --> 00:05:51,915
like a real grown man,

164
00:05:51,915 --> 00:05:54,415
there's still a child living inside him.

165
00:05:54,415 --> 00:05:57,065
Like a child who might be playful every day,

166
00:05:57,065 --> 00:05:58,490
and has his own world.

167
00:05:58,690 --> 00:05:59,540
And doesn't follow...

168
00:06:00,280 --> 00:06:01,580
He just doesn't play by the rules.

169
00:06:01,580 --> 00:06:02,880
That's exactly it.

170
00:06:03,030 --> 00:06:07,830
So sometimes everyone thinks he's the one with the biggest contrast.

171
00:06:07,830 --> 00:06:10,655
And sometimes he always breaks the norms.

172
00:06:10,655 --> 00:06:13,130
And does some unexpected things.

173
00:06:13,130 --> 00:06:15,905
Like during the last recording session,

174
00:06:15,905 --> 00:06:17,905
Baige was really attached to a stick.

175
00:06:17,905 --> 00:06:20,080
He was just obsessed with it.

176
00:06:20,140 --> 00:06:20,490
Yeah.

177
00:06:20,740 --> 00:06:23,140
Can you tell us the story of this stick?

178
00:06:23,740 --> 00:06:24,265
Actually,

179
00:06:24,265 --> 00:06:28,390
I think the behind-the-scenes footage also showed his love for the stick.

180
00:06:30,090 --> 00:06:33,315
Ever since he saw this stick,

181
00:06:33,315 --> 00:06:34,690
he kept playing with it in his hand.

182
00:06:34,990 --> 00:06:37,265
Last season, it was the little axe that Bai bought.

183
00:06:37,265 --> 00:06:40,790
And this season, it's that 150-centimeter stick.

184
00:06:42,310 --> 00:06:44,210
So what happened to the stick later?

185
00:06:44,460 --> 00:06:46,635
Did you send it to him?

186
00:06:46,635 --> 00:06:47,610
No, we didn't.

187
00:06:47,960 --> 00:06:48,860
In the end, it was left behind.

188
00:06:48,860 --> 00:06:54,860
I saw some netizens saying we must give him the stick.

189
00:06:54,860 --> 00:06:59,235
But actually, after the last recording,

190
00:06:59,235 --> 00:07:00,610
he said

191
00:07:00,700 --> 00:07:01,113
he wouldn't take it.

192
00:07:01,113 --> 00:07:02,375
So we asked him why.

193
00:07:02,375 --> 00:07:05,250
He said he wanted that feeling of loving something but not being able to have it.

194
00:07:06,500 --> 00:07:07,675
At first, I was already prepared

195
00:07:07,675 --> 00:07:10,675
and had told our props director

196
00:07:10,675 --> 00:07:12,150
that we must give him this stick.

197
00:07:12,150 --> 00:07:14,775
Because Baige's staff had said

198
00:07:14,775 --> 00:07:18,825
that the stick he liked must be given to him.

199
00:07:18,825 --> 00:07:21,475
We were considering whether to give him a new one.

200
00:07:21,475 --> 00:07:23,150
But his staff said

201
00:07:23,220 --> 00:07:24,670
he would definitely recognize this stick.

202
00:07:27,420 --> 00:07:31,820
You just mentioned that, for example, if you send something to Bai,

203
00:07:31,820 --> 00:07:33,745
like giving him something new,

204
00:07:33,745 --> 00:07:34,995
he would notice it right away.

205
00:07:34,995 --> 00:07:37,895
It's the same when he's solving cases.

206
00:07:37,895 --> 00:07:39,870
He can easily spot clues.

207
00:07:39,870 --> 00:07:41,370
And he's the one who connects them all together.

208
00:07:41,570 --> 00:07:43,820
He's very observant.

209
00:07:44,420 --> 00:07:47,570
He's the one who's aware of everyone's state in the room.

210
00:07:48,120 --> 00:07:51,320
Don't be fooled if you see him just playing around on the side sometimes.

211
00:07:51,320 --> 00:07:51,995
Or doing something else.

212
00:07:51,995 --> 00:07:54,845
But when it matters,

213
00:07:54,845 --> 00:07:58,170
he can still pick up on some important things.

214
00:07:58,370 --> 00:07:59,945
So it seems like he's offline, right?

215
00:07:59,945 --> 00:08:00,720
But actually, he's not.

216
00:08:01,060 --> 00:08:01,860
Yeah, that's right.

217
00:08:01,860 --> 00:08:02,960
Although sometimes,

218
00:08:02,960 --> 00:08:04,710
everyone says he doesn't talk much.

219
00:08:04,710 --> 00:08:07,760
It seems like he's just quietly on the side, not competing for anything.

220
00:08:07,810 --> 00:08:09,910
But actually, when he does speak,

221
00:08:09,910 --> 00:08:10,635
as long as he says something,

222
00:08:10,635 --> 00:08:12,435
it's usually right on point.

223
00:08:12,435 --> 00:08:15,210
And he understands the plot really quickly.

224
00:08:15,210 --> 00:08:17,510
If there's a problem, he'll reflect on it himself.

225
00:08:17,560 --> 00:08:18,710
Actually, this statement

226
00:08:18,710 --> 00:08:23,210
doesn't mean he's always combining each game session

227
00:08:23,210 --> 00:08:24,560
and the results

228
00:08:24,980 --> 00:08:29,655
to summarize his own issues—he'll also ask everyone, "Why did you vote for me this time?"

229
00:08:29,655 --> 00:08:31,080
Or, "What were you thinking?"

230
00:08:31,080 --> 00:08:32,680
Then he'll improve his own gameplay.

231
00:08:32,880 --> 00:08:33,280
Yeah.

232
00:08:33,480 --> 00:08:38,430
So when we look at Baige, there are still a lot of things that make him seem like a big kid.

233
00:08:38,430 --> 00:08:41,580
And when he saw the zombie theme,

234
00:08:41,580 --> 00:08:43,530
why did he keep going "awoo awoo"?

235
00:08:43,530 --> 00:08:48,230
Why did he choose to portray his character in that way?

236
00:08:48,700 --> 00:08:51,875
I remember asking him this question on the rooftop that day.

237
00:08:51,875 --> 00:08:56,200
Because I kept hearing his "awoo awoo awoo" through my earpiece.

238
00:08:56,550 --> 00:08:58,500
I thought it was pretty funny.

239
00:08:58,500 --> 00:08:58,850
So I was wondering,

240
00:08:58,850 --> 00:08:59,000
hmm,

241
00:08:59,000 --> 00:09:01,075
why did he suddenly start going "awoo"?

242
00:09:01,075 --> 00:09:02,250
Then he told me,

243
00:09:02,300 --> 00:09:02,950
he said,

244
00:09:02,950 --> 00:09:06,775
"When you NPCs showed up, you were always around me going 'awoo awoo awoo.'"

245
00:09:06,775 --> 00:09:08,100
And then he bit me, right?

246
00:09:08,480 --> 00:09:08,805
So I said,

247
00:09:08,805 --> 00:09:11,230
"Oh, so it was because you got infected by the 'awoo.'"

248
00:09:11,930 --> 00:09:16,180
And then there's the lively cuteness of zombies.

249
00:09:16,180 --> 00:09:18,705
And then there are some other times as well.

250
00:09:18,705 --> 00:09:20,655
Actually, my brother is quite mischievous too.

251
00:09:20,655 --> 00:09:21,405
How should I put it...

252
00:09:21,405 --> 00:09:24,780
For example, at the start of this season's pilot episode,

253
00:09:24,930 --> 00:09:27,930
when we were taking him to get ready for his appearance,

254
00:09:28,220 --> 00:09:28,570
then

255
00:09:28,570 --> 00:09:30,220
I saw my brother's publicity shoot.

256
00:09:30,270 --> 00:09:32,945
When they were about to take his picture with the camera,

257
00:09:32,945 --> 00:09:34,945
I didn't want to block his shot.

258
00:09:34,945 --> 00:09:35,170
So

259
00:09:35,170 --> 00:09:36,558
I moved to the side to get out of the way.

260
00:09:36,558 --> 00:09:37,020
Then

261
00:09:37,020 --> 00:09:39,545
After the publicity shoot was done,

262
00:09:39,545 --> 00:09:41,395
they showed me the photos.

263
00:09:41,395 --> 00:09:42,070
That's when I realized

264
00:09:42,070 --> 00:09:43,970
that when I moved aside,

265
00:09:43,970 --> 00:09:45,570
he also moved to the side with me.

266
00:09:45,900 --> 00:09:47,800
He even stood behind me on purpose as a joke.

267
00:09:47,800 --> 00:09:50,250
He was trying to stop the publicity staff from taking his picture.

268
00:09:50,400 --> 00:09:52,400
So the photos that came out

269
00:09:52,400 --> 00:09:54,825
only had half of him in them.

270
00:09:54,825 --> 00:09:56,600
It was just my big face in the front.

271
00:09:56,600 --> 00:09:57,900
And my hair was flying everywhere.

272
00:09:58,250 --> 00:09:59,550
So at that moment I said,

273
00:09:59,550 --> 00:10:01,150
"Why is my brother so mischievous?"

274
00:10:01,300 --> 00:10:03,600
His staff looked a bit helpless,

275
00:10:03,600 --> 00:10:05,150
but with affection, they said,

276
00:10:05,150 --> 00:10:06,150
"That's just how he is."

277
00:10:06,630 --> 00:10:07,780
It's actually pretty cute.

278
00:10:08,730 --> 00:10:12,005
From what I've seen, and from what you said before,

279
00:10:12,005 --> 00:10:13,455
he's actually quite rebellious.

280
00:10:13,455 --> 00:10:15,380
He really likes to say the opposite of what he means.

281
00:10:15,580 --> 00:10:17,980
Even in what we just talked about,

282
00:10:18,180 --> 00:10:19,830
you can see some of that.

283
00:10:19,830 --> 00:10:21,380
Yeah, I think so too.

284
00:10:21,840 --> 00:10:22,340
There was this one time,

285
00:10:22,340 --> 00:10:24,640
I remember when we played a game at the convenience store,

286
00:10:24,640 --> 00:10:25,865
he had to pick something.

287
00:10:25,865 --> 00:10:27,515
We recommended some food to him,

288
00:10:27,515 --> 00:10:28,690
some local snacks.

289
00:10:28,740 --> 00:10:29,515
But he said,

290
00:10:29,515 --> 00:10:30,915
"No, I won't take your suggestions.

291
00:10:30,915 --> 00:10:31,990
I want to pick the small folding stool."

292
00:10:32,040 --> 00:10:33,590
Then the next day, when we were filming another game,

293
00:10:33,590 --> 00:10:34,090
he said,

294
00:10:34,090 --> 00:10:35,690
"I shouldn't have picked this small folding stool.

295
00:10:35,690 --> 00:10:36,565
It's completely useless.

296
00:10:36,565 --> 00:10:37,365
I only sat on it once.

297
00:10:37,365 --> 00:10:38,590
There are stools everywhere anyway."

298
00:10:42,580 --> 00:10:45,830
Let's talk about Baige's styling.

299
00:10:45,830 --> 00:10:52,130
Many people have said that Baige's looks this season have a lot of clever details.

300
00:10:52,530 --> 00:10:56,530
The sunflower seed brooch, for example, is completely unique.

301
00:10:56,530 --> 00:10:57,930
That recent one, too.

302
00:10:57,930 --> 00:10:58,980
And those scales as well.

303
00:10:59,640 --> 00:11:01,690
The earrings in this one, too.

304
00:11:01,890 --> 00:11:03,015
Colorful feathers, colorful feathers.

305
00:11:03,015 --> 00:11:03,890
My Little Pony.

306
00:11:04,040 --> 00:11:08,065
You can't talk about it without mentioning My Little Pony.

307
00:11:08,065 --> 00:11:11,765
I think all of this is thanks to Baige's studio.

308
00:11:11,765 --> 00:11:13,040
Including the stylist.

309
00:11:13,140 --> 00:11:16,690
How can they make the looks stand out even more this season?

310
00:11:16,690 --> 00:11:18,890
So this season, he brought a lot of

311
00:11:19,420 --> 00:11:21,170
different and fresh styles.

312
00:11:21,170 --> 00:11:22,320
for us.

313
00:11:22,370 --> 00:11:23,770
Which one impressed you the most?

314
00:11:23,970 --> 00:11:25,270
The one that impressed me the most...

315
00:11:25,270 --> 00:11:25,595
Hmm.

316
00:11:25,595 --> 00:11:26,670
Which one do you like best?

317
00:11:27,820 --> 00:11:29,195
I like every single one.

318
00:11:29,195 --> 00:11:32,320
I like them all—I'm even pouring water now.

319
00:11:32,720 --> 00:11:35,920
Because each look really feels different.

320
00:11:35,920 --> 00:11:37,395
When trying on the makeup,

321
00:11:37,395 --> 00:11:38,420
he was quite happy too.

322
00:11:38,890 --> 00:11:39,340
For example,

323
00:11:39,340 --> 00:11:40,840
for the pirate episode,

324
00:11:42,640 --> 00:11:45,215
we prepared a long wig for him.

325
00:11:45,215 --> 00:11:48,390
It was like Captain Jack's wig.

326
00:11:48,940 --> 00:11:50,340
Then we started the fitting.

327
00:11:50,440 --> 00:11:52,090
He put on the wig himself.

328
00:11:52,090 --> 00:11:53,140
Wrapped the scarf around his head.

329
00:11:53,240 --> 00:11:54,740
He had a full beard at the time.

330
00:11:55,640 --> 00:11:57,140
He looked like Captain Jack,

331
00:11:57,140 --> 00:11:58,190
but also like a rocker.

332
00:11:59,160 --> 00:11:59,935
It was about him.

333
00:11:59,935 --> 00:12:02,810
He was in front of the mirror, shaking his head and moving around, you know?

334
00:12:02,810 --> 00:12:05,360
He felt really rock and roll.

335
00:12:05,360 --> 00:12:05,760
Yeah.

336
00:12:05,760 --> 00:12:07,810
Later, since it might be too hot,

337
00:12:07,810 --> 00:12:10,410
or maybe staying in it all day would feel stuffy,

338
00:12:10,410 --> 00:12:12,635
he gave up on that look.

339
00:12:12,635 --> 00:12:18,810
I hope we can see him take on this kind of challenge somewhere else or in the next episode.

340
00:12:19,660 --> 00:12:20,535
And also,

341
00:12:20,535 --> 00:12:22,560
besides the styling,

342
00:12:22,560 --> 00:12:27,785
he actually has a lot of other little creative ideas for his character.

343
00:12:27,785 --> 00:12:29,035
Like in the red carpet episode,

344
00:12:29,035 --> 00:12:30,660
do you mean the signature he designed?

345
00:12:31,010 --> 00:12:33,135
That signature was

346
00:12:33,135 --> 00:12:34,710
I think he asked about it at the time.

347
00:12:34,760 --> 00:12:37,485
Then I said, "You’re going to sign on camera soon."

348
00:12:37,485 --> 00:12:39,410
I asked, "Do you want to practice that signature?"

349
00:12:40,060 --> 00:12:40,635
He just said it at the start.

350
00:12:40,635 --> 00:12:41,635
He just said it offhandedly.

351
00:12:41,635 --> 00:12:42,360
No need.

352
00:12:42,360 --> 00:12:43,960
Then later he thought about it.

353
00:12:44,010 --> 00:12:44,385
Oh,

354
00:12:44,385 --> 00:12:45,360
since he was just sitting there with nothing to do anyway,

355
00:12:45,360 --> 00:12:46,110
he decided to practice a bit.

356
00:12:46,110 --> 00:12:47,960
Then someone gave him a piece of paper.

357
00:12:48,060 --> 00:12:51,660
He practiced for a whole page of A4 paper.

358
00:12:51,660 --> 00:12:55,810
After that, he designed a cursive signature he was quite satisfied with.

359
00:12:55,810 --> 00:12:57,210
He was pretty proud of it.

360
00:12:57,310 --> 00:12:57,635
Yeah.

361
00:12:57,635 --> 00:12:59,960
He added some little creative touches to his character.

362
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:00,250
Right.

363
00:13:00,300 --> 00:13:02,675
So does he usually do that with costumes,

364
00:13:02,675 --> 00:13:04,575
or with some lines as well?

365
00:13:04,575 --> 00:13:05,375
Does he do that too?

366
00:13:05,375 --> 00:13:06,900
As for designing lines,

367
00:13:07,050 --> 00:13:08,800
he doesn't do anything in advance.

368
00:13:08,800 --> 00:13:13,150
He does it in those specific situations, like they talk about in acting classes.

369
00:13:13,150 --> 00:13:15,650
Yeah, when he feels inspired in the moment.

370
00:13:15,650 --> 00:13:16,725
For example,

371
00:13:16,725 --> 00:13:18,113
when he said "sir, great righteousness,"

372
00:13:18,113 --> 00:13:20,625
while bowing to Director Dan,

373
00:13:20,625 --> 00:13:21,800
and said "a sense of righteousness arises,"

374
00:13:21,800 --> 00:13:23,050
it felt like he was about to sacrifice himself.

375
00:13:23,050 --> 00:13:24,200
He was about to become a monster too.

376
00:13:24,260 --> 00:13:29,410
Or when the music and ritual troupe said the house wasn't clean,

377
00:13:29,410 --> 00:13:30,485
he automatically got into character.

378
00:13:30,485 --> 00:13:33,510
Like, "What do you mean saying our house isn't clean in front of us?"

379
00:13:33,510 --> 00:13:36,860
When it comes to costume designs that help him get into character,

380
00:13:36,860 --> 00:13:38,810
he also gives his own suggestions.

381
00:13:39,110 --> 00:13:40,210
For example,

382
00:13:40,760 --> 00:13:40,935
Yeah.

383
00:13:40,935 --> 00:13:41,835
The pirate episode.

384
00:13:41,835 --> 00:13:44,685
He thought the collar was a turn-down collar.

385
00:13:44,685 --> 00:13:46,360
He felt a stand-up collar would look better.

386
00:13:46,360 --> 00:13:48,185
At that time, the pants were also too big.

387
00:13:48,185 --> 00:13:50,510
Everyone wondered if they should make them smaller.

388
00:13:50,510 --> 00:13:52,960
Then Bai Ge looked in the mirror.

389
00:13:52,960 --> 00:13:55,235
He said, compared to making them smaller,

390
00:13:55,235 --> 00:13:58,535
wouldn't tucking the pant legs into the boots look cooler?

391
00:13:58,535 --> 00:13:59,510
That's the vibe.

392
00:13:59,510 --> 00:14:01,310
He gives a lot of his own suggestions.

393
00:14:01,560 --> 00:14:01,835
And then,

394
00:14:01,835 --> 00:14:02,810
we noticed that

395
00:14:02,810 --> 00:14:07,810
this season, Bai Ge has formed a special bond with the drone.

396
00:14:07,910 --> 00:14:08,498
Yeah.

397
00:14:08,498 --> 00:14:11,560
It started from the pilot episode, I think.

398
00:14:12,360 --> 00:14:14,085
We actually predicted

399
00:14:14,085 --> 00:14:16,535
which prop would be the most fun for each person.

400
00:14:16,535 --> 00:14:18,285
At the time, I had a feeling

401
00:14:18,285 --> 00:14:20,485
that Bai Ge might end up with the drone.

402
00:14:20,485 --> 00:14:23,410
He always has a different style from everyone else.

403
00:14:23,410 --> 00:14:25,160
And he really did get the drone.

404
00:14:25,660 --> 00:14:27,160
We were even preparing

405
00:14:27,260 --> 00:14:29,535
that if any guest didn't know how to use it,

406
00:14:29,535 --> 00:14:31,485
they could ask the cameraman for help.

407
00:14:31,485 --> 00:14:32,660
We hadn't even told him yet.

408
00:14:32,660 --> 00:14:35,285
But he just fiddled with it himself for a few minutes.

409
00:14:35,285 --> 00:14:36,123
And then he figured it out.

410
00:14:36,123 --> 00:14:38,285
He didn't use it much this episode.

411
00:14:38,285 --> 00:14:43,660
But he's already skilled enough to use the drone to film cinematic shots for everyone.

412
00:14:44,630 --> 00:14:48,080
At the time, I thought he really liked this drone.

413
00:14:48,080 --> 00:14:50,880
So this time, on his birthday,

414
00:14:51,130 --> 00:14:54,030
we specially gave him a sign-in card

415
00:14:54,030 --> 00:14:55,355
and the same model of that drone.

416
00:14:55,355 --> 00:14:57,630
He also loves eating sunflower seeds.

417
00:14:57,830 --> 00:14:59,880
So we bought a lot at that time,

418
00:14:59,930 --> 00:15:03,380
all kinds of flavors of sunflower seeds for him.

419
00:15:03,380 --> 00:15:05,730
It probably covered his sunflower seeds for a whole year.

420
00:15:06,370 --> 00:15:07,870
That kind of made up for him.

421
00:15:07,870 --> 00:15:09,720
Later, he complained

422
00:15:09,720 --> 00:15:10,745
that he didn't get to eat the sunflower seeds.

423
00:15:10,745 --> 00:15:13,470
Yeah, he kept mumbling about it.

424
00:15:13,720 --> 00:15:15,995
Saying things like the sunflower seeds were all gone.

425
00:15:15,995 --> 00:15:16,995
So I guess we made it up to him.

426
00:15:16,995 --> 00:15:17,720
Yeah.

427
00:15:18,320 --> 00:15:21,020
Let's ask the last question.

428
00:15:21,170 --> 00:15:25,270
Bai Ge actually recorded 10 episodes with us this season.

429
00:15:25,570 --> 00:15:29,745
Did he ever share his feelings about each recording with you?

